# 1. 神山高校芸術祭

Female Students: Hey, An, check this out! It's apparently one of the parfaits you can get at carino/carina...
An: Whoa, that's gigantic! I mean, just look at all the strawberries... Is it even possible to finish it?
Female Students: Three of us should be able to if we work together! We should go sometime since it's been going totally viral on TrickTrick!
Male Students: Hey, Akito! You free after school today?
Akito: No, but why...?
Male Students: I found this cool shop that I was thinking about checking out! I know you're busy with practice, but we need to hang out more!
Nene: (This class is never quiet...)
Nene: (I was hoping to do some reading before our long homeroom started, but I won't be able to focus with all this noise...)
Nene: *Sigh* (I guess I'll just listen to some music instead while I wait for the teacher to get here.)
Teacher: Okay, everyone, take your seats.
An: Oh, see you guys later!
Female Students: See you! We'll talk again later.
Male Students: So, what are we gonna do during the long homeroom today?
Teacher: Oh, about that. I have something very important to discuss with you all today.
Nene: (Something important...?)
Teacher: Starting this year, we will be holding an event called the “Kamiyama High School Arts Festival”.
Akito: An arts festival?
Teacher: As you all know, this school prides itself on fostering creativity and freedom of expression. Because of that, we're always receiving and coming up with ideas for new school events.
Teacher: For this festival, with creativity and cooperation in mind, the students in each class will work together to produce and present an artistic piece.
Teacher: These presentations will be ranked the day of, and we also plan on inviting a famed figure to serve as a special judge...
Female Students: Wait, a famed figure...? You're talking about a celebrity, right?! Who are you guys inviting?!
An: Also, you said, “An artistic piece.” Can you tell us a little more about that...?
Teacher: Of course. There aren't any strict rules to speak of...
Teacher: As long as you all work together with a spirit of cooperation in mind, you'll basically be free to do whatever you like.
Teacher: To name a few examples, you could do a play, put on a small concert, make a movie or perform a dance... Producing a sculpture together could also be fun.
Nene: (We're free to choose whatever...?)
Nene: (A play or a concert... So I might be able to sing? That'd definitely get me interested...)
Nene: (But we all have to work together... Not exactly my strong suit.)
Female Students: This sounds super fun!!!
An: Yeah! It's like we get to have another school festival!
Nene: (Yeah, I should've known they'd react this way...)
Female Students: What should we do? I really wanna make a film together!
Female Students: Me too! Making one as a class could be a way to make the most of our youth!
An: Youth, huh...? I don't know about that, but a film would definitely be memorable since it'll pretty much last forever.
Male Students: Yeah! I'm not hearing any other ideas, so let's make a film together!
Nene: (A film...?)
Nene: (Is it possible for a bunch of amateurs to actually make one...? It sounds like a lot of work...)
Akito: Hold on a second... Making one isn't as easy as you guys are making it sound.
Nene: ...!
Akito: I don't know much about filmmaking, but I'm guessing it's gonna take a lot of time and effort. We should plan things out a little better before we decide.
Nene: (Yeah, exactly...!)
An: Hmm... He has a point. It might be good for us to appoint a leader, like a director. Someone with experience or who knows a lot about this stuff...
Female Students: Someone who knows a lot...
Female Students: Oh! I know the perfect person!
Nene: (The perfect person? Who...?)
Female Students: Kusanagi! Could you be our director?!
Nene: Huh...?
Nene: M-Me...?! Why...?
Female Students: You're in the film club, right? And you perform in shows!
Female Students: You seem like the right person for the job since you have a ton of knowledge and experience when it comes to films and acting!
Nene: Th-Thanks, but... For the film club, we just watch the movies we have in our room...
Nene: Plus, acting for a stage performance and acting in a film are two different things. I really don't know if I could be a director...
Female Students: Really? But...
An: Alright, hold your horses! You're making her panic. We can't just ask her to do this all of a sudden.
Female Students: Yeah, you're right... Sorry, Kusanagi. I didn't mean to sound so pushy.
Nene: N-No, uh... That's okay...
Female Students: But I do think that you're the best choice out of everyone in this class to become the director...
Nene: Huh...?
Female Students: I saw you perform in a show at PXL a little while ago, and I was blown away by how good it was!
Female Students: You guys come up with those shows all on your own, right? I figured if you know how to make something that amazing, then you'd be able to do the same for our film.
Female Students: So, you don't have to if you don't want to... But will you at least think about it?
Nene: Oh...
Nene: (Right. Some of them have seen our shows.)
Nene: (To be fair, I did help come up with a few of those stories, so I might be a little more experienced than everyone else...)
Nene: (But I've never made a film before. Not only that...)
Nene: (The director has to get everyone to move as a unit while staying on schedule for production, right?)
Nene: (I-I'm supposed to get all these chatterboxes to work as a team...?)
An: How do you feel, Kusanagi...? Again, you don't have to if you don't want to.
Nene: Y-Yeah, I know...
Nene: (But...)
Nene: (Opportunities to lead big teams like this don't come around often, so maybe I should accept.)
Nene: (Also, I can't be afraid of working with new people...)
Nene: (We're gonna be working with other troupes moving forward... And my goal's to become a world-class musical actress.)
Nene: I-I'll do it.
Nene: It'll be a good experience for me... So if you're all okay with it, I think I'll take the job...
Female Students: Really?! Thanks so much, Kusanagi!
Nene: Y-You're welcome...
Nene: (W-Well, I just agreed...)
Nene: (There's no turning back now... And if we're making a film, I wanna make it a good one...)
Nene: (I-I've gotta do my best. For the sake of the festival...!)
